Course gives an overview about terminology and theories used in tourism geography. Students will conduct individual assignments and group works to practice theoretical knowledge gained in the lecture. Important part of the course is to learn to find and use relevant information sources (e.g., scientific articles, open data, reports etc) for independent and group work.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give an overview about the basic theoretical concepts, reasearch fields and methods used in tourism geography. To introduce the variety of tourism types and tourism destinations. Throughout the learning process the focus is on independent work: searching for information, analysing and evaluating the validity and reliability of the information.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After successful passing the student: 1) uses tourism geography`s basic terminology in relevant discussions orally and in written; 2) name and explains the theories and methods used in tourism geography and the important studies and researchers; 3) describes and compares the main tourism types and their geographies in the world and in Estonia; 4) illustrates the importance of place and space in tourism geography; 5) characterizes and compares the economic, social and environmental impacts of tourism; 5) is able to look for information, analyse and critically evaluate its correctness.
